<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>What Happens Next</title>
  <style>
    {{{print_css}}}

    @page {
      size: A4;
      margin: 12mm;
    }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      color: #1f1635;
      font-size: 10pt;
      line-height: 1.55;
    }

    .hero,
    .step-card,
    .handoff-box {
      page-break-inside: avoid;
      break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .hero {
      border: 1px solid #ddd6fe;
      background: #faf8ff;
      padding: 1.2em;
      margin-bottom: 1em;
    }

    .hero h1 {
      margin: 0 0 0.2em 0;
      font-size: 18pt;
    }

    .hero h2 {
      margin: 0 0 0.35em 0;
      font-size: 11pt;
      color: #5b5370;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    }

    .hero p {
      margin: 0.25em 0;
    }

    .steps {
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.9em;
    }

    .step-card,
    .handoff-box {
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      background: #fff;
      padding: 1em;
    }

    .step-number {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 0.45em;
      padding: 0.18em 0.55em;
      border-radius: 0;
      background: #ede9fe;
      color: #4c1d95;
      font-size: 8.5pt;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .step-card h3,
    .handoff-box h3 {
      margin: 0 0 0.4em 0;
      font-size: 10.5pt;
      color: #231942;
    }

    .step-card p,
    .handoff-box p {
      margin: 0.3em 0;
    }

    .muted {
      color: #6b7280;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="hero">
    <h2>{{pack_title}}</h2>
    <h1>What Happens Next</h1>
    <p><strong>{{status_label}}</strong></p>
    <p>{{next_step_text}}</p>
  </div>

  <div class="steps">
    {{#each next_steps}}
    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-number">Step {{step}}</div>
      <h3>{{title}}</h3>
      <p>{{detail}}</p>
    </div>
    {{/each}}
  </div>

  <div class="handoff-box">
    {{#if (eq pack_stage "stage1")}}
    <h3>Stage 2 handoff</h3>
    <p>If this proceeds to court, the Stage 2 Court & Possession Pack builds directly on this file.</p>
    <p class="muted">The same notice, service record, arrears position, and core facts should carry forward without being rebuilt from scratch.</p>
    {{else}}
    <h3>After court preparation</h3>
    <p>Keep the issued claim, service record, hearing bundle, and any later enforcement papers aligned in the same case file.</p>
    <p class="muted">This pack completes the case started in Stage 1 and is structured to be used as a single continuous file. The stronger the continuity between notice, claim, hearing, and enforcement, the less room there is for avoidable procedural challenge.</p>
    {{/if}}
  </div>
</body>
</html>
